♪ Ardent looking, 
patient search, ♪

17
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:19,250
♪ Find the truth we need... ♪

18
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,458
♪ Open soul... Open eyes... ♪

19
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:27,458
♪ Divining world
wherein truth lies... ♪

20
00:05:27,541 --> 00:05:30,958
♪ Patient looking,
ardent search, ♪

21
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:35,708
♪ Nature, hear our call... ♪

22
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:39,250
♪ Ardent looking,
patient search, ♪

23
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:43,833
♪ Water, hear our plea... ♪

24
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:47,208
♪ Open soul... Open eyes... ♪

25
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:52,125
♪ Divining world
wherein truth lies... ♪

26
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:55,583
♪ Patient looking,
ardent search, ♪

27
00:05:55,666 --> 00:05:59,791
♪ Searching for the truth... ♪

28
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:03,875
♪ Ardent looking,
patient search, ♪

29
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:09,291
♪ Find the truth we need... ♪

30
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:11,875
[PERCUSSIVE CHIMING]

31
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:14,541
[KIRARA]
The water has spoken. How many?

32
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:17,541
Seven tablets.

33
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,875
Dig seven times with seven turns

34
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:21,625
where the Dowsing 
Crystal points.

35
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:23,208
The water will be waiting.

36
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:26,333
Will it definitely
be enough for a well?

37
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:27,875
This will sure help us out.

38
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:30,000
Yeah, I was scared
when the well dried up--

39
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:32,166
I thought it was the last
thing our village could take.

40
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:34,750
But the Priestess
has saved us.

41
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,666
[MANZO GRUNTS]

42
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,958
Thank you for your help.
We would be lost without you.

43
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:42,500
She helps us with everything.

44
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:48,291
Hey what's the matter, Komachi?

45
00:06:48,375 --> 00:06:49,541
[KOMACHI WHINES]

46
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:52,333
My stomach's growling!

47
00:06:52,416 --> 00:06:55,041
[KIRARA LAUGHS]

48
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:56,875
[KIRARA SIGHS]

49
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,083
[KIRARA GASPS]

50
00:06:58,166 --> 00:07:08,791
[RUMBLING]

51
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:10,000
[RIKICHI]
Why are they here?

52
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:12,625
They know it's not
harvesting season yet.

53
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:14,791
[MOSUKE] They take
more than rice now.

54
00:07:14,875 --> 00:07:17,291
I heard of another village where
they took their livestock--

55
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:19,625
and then they came back
and took their women too,

56
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,666
daughters, wives,
it didn't matter.

57
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,750
They took them all.

58
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,166
[RIKICHI] Then we have to
get the Water Priestess

59
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:26,041
to the shrine!

60
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,666
What if they see her?

61
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:31,291
[MOSUKE]
Cursed Bandits...

62
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,166
[RIKICHI] It's almost
harvesting season.

63
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,541
They probably came today to
see how the rice was growing--

64
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,583
to see how much
they could get.

65
00:08:06,666 --> 00:08:09,166
[MOSUKE] I can't believe
it's already been a year.

66
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,125
[MANZO] And they're going
to take it all again.

67
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,750
[RIKICHI]
It gets worse every year.

68
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,875
It's like negotiating
with wolves. 

69
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,333
You give them your arms,
then they ask for your legs!

70
00:08:17,416 --> 00:08:20,750
Can't we do something?
I can't sleep anymore. 

71
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,041
Every night, I think
I hear them coming. 

72
00:08:23,125 --> 00:08:25,500
I hear that rumbling 
of their machines.

73
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:29,583
[YOHEI] We're all suffering. 
But what can we do?

74
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,125
[RIKICHI] We have 
to fight the Bandits.

75
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:32,708
Rise up and kill
them ourselves!

76
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,666
[MOSUKE] Kill the No-Buseri?
That's madness.

77
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,083
[RIKICHI] It's the only
way we'll keep them from

78
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,166
taking all we have!

79
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:40,708
[YOHEI]
How can we battle them?!

80
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:43,416
We're just farmers, and they're
the Bandits! The No-Buseri!

81
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,333
They've turned themselves
into weapons--

82
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:48,708
they fly in giant machines,
with swords the size of houses!

83
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:50,375
They rule over everything!

84
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,041
[RIKICHI] So we should
break our backs all year,

85
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:54,333
just so they can
have fat stomachs?

86
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,125
[MANZO] It's like an
earthquake, Rikichi.

87
00:08:56,208 --> 00:08:59,416
All we can do is bear it, and
give the Bandits what they want.

88
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,208
Other villages have
tried to fight back,

89
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,833
and they were massacred.

90
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:05,666
It's better to lose
our rice than our lives.

91
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:06,791
[MANZO YELLS]

92
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:07,958
[RIKICHI]
What are you talking about?

93
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:09,083
Without the crop,
we'll be dead anyway!

94
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:10,291
[MOSUKE]
Rikichi, please. Stop.

95
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,500
[RIKICHI] No. We can't
be cowards anymore!

96
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:15,166
[MOSUKE] I know you're mad,
but we've all had losses.

97
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:17,083
[RIKICHI]
You haven't lost anything!

98
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:19,541
[ELDER]
We'll fight them.

99
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:26,875
We'll make our stand...
Against the Bandits.

100
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:28,208
Elder,
that's impossible!

101
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:29,250
We're rice growers--

102
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:30,750
We don't know
anything about war!

103
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,291
That's why we're hiring Samurai.

104
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:34,333
[GASPING]

105
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:38,666
[VILLAGERS MURMUR WORRIEDLY]

106
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,833
But I've never heard 
of a village of peasants

107
00:09:40,916 --> 00:09:43,208
hiring samurai, Elder.

108
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,916
I have witnessed it
with my own eyes,

109
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,291
after the Great War 
ended, and the Bandits

110
00:09:47,375 --> 00:09:50,208
pillaged the countryside
completely unchecked... 

111
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,833
Out of all the
villages that I passed,

112
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:54,416
only one had not
been burned to the soil,

113
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,250
one that had hired Samurai--

114
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,750
Only <i>they</i> can
compete with Bandits.

115
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:01,041
[RIKICHI] Yes, Elder, of course!
That's what we have to do!

116
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:02,791
[MANZO] But Samurai
are expensive and proud, 

117
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:05,083
and the only thing we have
of value is the harvest.

118
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,833
I doubt they're going
to fight to save us

119
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:09,416
in the name of sympathy
and a few bowls of rice.

120
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:11,375
[ELDER]
Then find hungry samurai.

121
00:10:11,458 --> 00:10:12,958
[VILLAGERS]
Huh...?

122
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:15,541
Even bears will come out of the
forest if they're hungry enough.

123
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,000
[GOSAKU]
But if we really want Samurai,

124
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,416
then someone will
have to go into the city.

125
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,666
[MOSUKE]
And that's dangerous, too!

126
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,416
[RIKICHI]
Then I volunteer.

127
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:32,458
[ELDER]
Ahh... Very good, Rikichi.

128
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:34,291
[KIRARA] Elder?

129
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:37,958
I'd like to go too,
if you'll let me.

130
00:10:38,041 --> 00:10:39,416
[MATRIARCH]
Kirara, please.

131
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,833
I must... I can use
my talents to divine

132
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:45,250
which Samurai are most
suited for saving us.

133
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:48,541
No one questions
your abilities, Priestess,

134
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:50,875
but Samurai don't
behave like water...

135
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:52,875
Besides, the city is
dangerous for anyone,

136
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:54,583
especially
young girls...

137
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:58,250
I'm not afraid of it...
And Rikichi will be with me.

138
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:06,583
Of course, I trust
your wisdom over mine.

139
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,125
Then it's decided...

140
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:11,708
We are counting on you
as always, Water Priestess.

141
00:11:11,791 --> 00:11:13,333
I know.

142
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:16,666
Before the ears of
rice begin to bend,

143
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:19,333
bring us Samurai
who can defend us...

144
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:23,125
Our hope... Now rests on that.

145
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:40,541
You girls don't need to worry.
I'll protect you with my life.

146
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:42,583
And we are grateful
for that, Rikichi.

147
00:11:42,666 --> 00:11:44,375
I'm not worried at all, sis.

148
00:11:44,458 --> 00:11:46,375
I know your crystal
will find them.

149
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:48,750
You were very sweet
to come along, Komachi.

150
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,541
I wanted to
go exploring too,

151
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:52,333
and see the whole
big rest of the world.

152
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,666
I can't let you have
all the fun on your own.

153
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:57,625
So that's why...
I thought you wanted to help.

154
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:53,500
[HISSING]

155
00:12:58,916 --> 00:13:01,708
[DOGS BARK]

156
00:13:33,083 --> 00:13:35,916
Oh boy... That smells good.

157
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,958
[RIKICHI GRUNTS]

158
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,000
[KIRARA GASPS]

159
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:19,583
[RIKICHI]
The rice...

160
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,750
Thief! Stop!

161
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,041
[RIKICHI]
Please, that's our rice!

162
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:32,041
Help us, somebody!
Thief!

163
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:33,250
Stop whispering
and walking

164
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:35,041
and pretending like
you don't even hear!

165
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:37,666
Just somebody
stop him, please!

166
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,000
Catch the thief!

167
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:47,208
[THIEF YELLS]

168
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:51,458
[RIKICHI BREATHES HEAVILY]

169
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:56,250
[KATSUSHIRO] You're lucky
I'm not turning you in.

170
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,708
[RIKICHI] Oh, Great Samurai,
thank you so much...

171
00:14:58,791 --> 00:15:00,625
We don't deserve
your graciousness.

172
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:03,791
Please, get up, it
wasn't that big of a deal.

173
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:07,041
Get away from that...!

174
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:09,791
That's our rice!
Please, stop it! Stop!

175
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:12,291
[KATSUSHIRO]
Leave this man alone!

176
00:15:12,375 --> 00:15:14,291
[MEN YELL FEARFULLY]

177
00:15:18,916 --> 00:15:21,500
No...
Our precious rice...

178
00:15:21,583 --> 00:15:24,291
[RIKICHI]
Just help... It's okay now...

179
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:34,000
I was afraid... it was gone...

180
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:42,958
I'm... hungry...

181
00:15:43,041 --> 00:15:47,791
And we almost lost it...
We almost lost it all...

182
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:49,791
But we didn't,
Komachi, okay?

183
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:53,125
But what if we did?
Then we wouldn't have anything!

184
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:18,416
No, Great Samurai, please!

185
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,875
Don't get on your
hands and knees for us.

186
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:21,625
We can pick it up on our own.

187
00:16:21,708 --> 00:16:24,166
You're going to embarrass me
if you keep talking like that. 

188
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:27,958
It's a part of Bushido to
help those in need... Here.

189
00:16:28,041 --> 00:16:29,333
Thank you.

190
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,000
[KOMACHI]
Thanks for everything!

191
00:16:43,083 --> 00:16:45,750
[KIRARA] Yes, we owe
you a great deal now.

192
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:47,083
[KATSUSHIRO]
Some advice;

193
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,750
don't walk around with your
rice in plain view.

194
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:51,291
Find a safe place to stay,
away from all the crowds.

195
00:16:51,375 --> 00:16:52,666
[KIRARA] We will.

196
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,541
[KATSUSHIRO] I wish you the
best of luck. Farewell.

197
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:57,666
[RIKICHI] Wait, Great Samurai,
can we ask you something?

198
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:58,708
Go ahead.

199
00:16:58,791 --> 00:17:00,875
We wanted to, uh--

200
00:17:00,958 --> 00:17:03,333
No...
He isn't the one.

201
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:13,708
Are you sure, Priestess?

202
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:15,666
He is a samurai, and he's
stopped one thief already--

203
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:18,375
and he seems
perfectly willing to help.

204
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:20,125
The Dowsing Crystal
didn't choose him.

205
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:22,708
He doesn't have
the scent of battle.

206
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:35,958
[HOTEL KEEPER]
Rooms to rent for the night!

207
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:38,875
Clean floors and fair rates.
Don't miss out!

208
00:17:38,958 --> 00:17:40,916
[ONLOOKER] Come on! He's holed
up at the end of the street!

209
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,500
Sounds like there's
some trouble down there...

210
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:43,875
Huh...?

211
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:48,250
[KOMACHI]
Sister, wait!

212
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:49,333
[SHOP WOMAN]
Please, help us.

213
00:17:49,416 --> 00:17:51,291
My child's in there.

214
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:52,541
[KATSUSHIRO]
Can you tell me what happened?

215
00:17:52,625 --> 00:17:54,125
[SHOP MAN]
A burglar broke into our shop.

216
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,041
He was sneaking
around in the back.

217
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:57,791
I found him, and
I tried to scare him off,

218
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:59,333
but he grabbed the baby--

219
00:17:59,416 --> 00:18:02,166
he said he'd kill our child
if we called the authorities.

220
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,458
[KATSUSHIRO]
Then it's just the one man?

221
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,666
Yes, and he's still inside!

222
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,833
[KOMACHI]
Hey... is that the same one?

223
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,583
[KATSUSHIRO]
All right. I'll do what I can.

224
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:14,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hold on there, boy...

225
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:18,125
You're going to need some
muscle in a battle like this.

226
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:19,541
I'll help you out.

227
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:20,833
A battle...?

228
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:22,250
Look, I mean
no offense,

229
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:23,791
but this
isn't warfare...

230
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:25,666
It's just a
burglary gone wrong.

231
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:26,958
[KIKUCHIYO] Right...

232
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:29,875
<i>Everything's</i> a battle, kid.

233
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:33,208
Hey, shopkeeper, I might have
to crack a few eggs here--

234
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:35,291
Lose the shop to save the kid.

235
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:38,250
But you're not going to raise
a stink about that, are you?

236
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:41,125
[SHOP MAN] No, please--
Whatever it takes!

237
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:43,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
Very good. You're a wise man.

238
00:18:43,791 --> 00:18:46,625
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

239
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:51,416
[CROWD MURMURS]

240
00:18:53,583 --> 00:19:01,916
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

241
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:20,291
[BABY CRIES]

242
00:19:20,375 --> 00:19:21,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
The standoff's over...

243
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:23,583
Hand me the kid.

244
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:25,791
Wait, you're a samurai,
aren't you?

245
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,375
[KIKUCHIYO]
'Course I am!

246
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:30,125
Now, why'd you go causing
all this trouble?

247
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:32,958
If you were really a samurai,
you'd know that answer...

248
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:34,875
I haven't seen
food in a week... 

249
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:36,750
I've been on the
street since the war!

250
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,541
I had greater
ambitions that that! 

251
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:41,875
I was supposed to be an officer,
not some beggar in the slums!

252
00:19:41,958 --> 00:19:43,250
[KIKUCHIYO] How sad...

253
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:46,500
I'm warning you!
Keep away from me!

254
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:49,958
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

255
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:54,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Huh...?!

256
00:19:54,333 --> 00:20:01,750
[CROWD MURMURS WORRIEDLY]

257
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:04,875
What's wrong,
samurai...?

258
00:20:04,958 --> 00:20:08,166
If you want to save 
the kid, then strike me now!

259
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:17,791
[CROWD YELLS FEARFULLY]

260
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:19,833
Stay away...!
I'm not bluffing!

261
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:21,041
Stay away...!

262
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,208
Maybe you're afraid
to die, but I'm not...!

263
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:26,083
If the battles are over,
I'll start one here!

264
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:28,625
[KIKUCHIYO] What are you
talking about, you senile mule!

265
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:30,541
This isn't a battle!
It's just a burglary! 

266
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:33,916
Just a burglary gone wrong!

267
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,208
It's high time
I found you... Samurai.

268
00:20:41,916 --> 00:20:44,416
You don't recognize me...?
I'm not surprised. 

269
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:47,416
The name's Zaemon
Yoshichika the Peaceable.

270
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:50,666
I was only a boy when
you killed my parents.

271
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,875
I've devoted my life
to their vengeance--

272
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:55,333
and though I wasn't
expecting to find you today,

273
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:57,625
it's an opportunity
I won't turn down.

274
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:58,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
What are you talking about?

275
00:20:58,666 --> 00:20:59,583
[KAMBEI]
Don't deny it.

276
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:00,875
I could never
forget that armor.

277
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,083
Hey... What is this?

278
00:21:02,166 --> 00:21:04,583
You are, without
a doubt, my sworn nemesis...

279
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:07,166
Tsukumozaka
Jurobei Mitsuharu!

280
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:08,291
[KIKUCHIYO] Wait!

281
00:21:17,625 --> 00:21:19,000
[THUD]

282
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,375
Unbelievable...

283
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:29,750
Forgive me...
I don't mean to intrude.

284
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:32,625
Just... stay away...!
You hear me?!

285
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:43,833
[BABY CRIES]

286
00:21:43,916 --> 00:21:45,375
[THUD]

287
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:48,750
There, there, child...
You're all right now.

288
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,166
My sweet Kotaro...!

289
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:54,916
Oh, thank goodness
you're okay...

290
00:21:58,708 --> 00:22:01,541
[STATIC]

291
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:03,583
[SHOP MAN] Great samurai,
I can't thank you enough.

292
00:22:03,666 --> 00:22:05,333
You've saved my family...

293
00:22:05,416 --> 00:22:08,291
Let me offer you something
--a drink, perhaps?

294
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:09,875
[KAMBEI] You don't need
to thank me at all.

295
00:22:09,958 --> 00:22:11,416
You never asked
me to get involved. 

296
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,041
I'm just a nosy man...

297
00:22:13,125 --> 00:22:14,416
Now excuse me...

298
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,375
[KIKUCHIYO DISTORTED]
Hey! Wait!

299
00:22:17,458 --> 00:22:19,375
That hurt you bastard!

300
00:22:19,458 --> 00:22:22,083
How dare you use me
to get to that thief!

301
00:22:22,166 --> 00:22:24,500
Maybe we should
be sworn enemies!

302
00:22:24,583 --> 00:22:25,958
[CROWD GASPS]

303
00:22:29,708 --> 00:22:31,833
You say you're a samurai.
I have my doubts.

304
00:22:31,916 --> 00:22:33,083
[KIKUCHIYO] What?!

305
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:35,750
You carry a sword,
yet you hesitate.

306
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:38,500
[KIKUCHIYO DISTORTED]
Don't walk away from me!

307
00:22:38,583 --> 00:22:41,583
We're not... finished yet!

308
00:22:41,666 --> 00:22:44,833
Hey, what are you fooling
around for, you headless beast?

309
00:22:44,916 --> 00:22:47,000
Bend down and pick me up!

310
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:58,875
Priestess, slow down...

311
00:23:00,666 --> 00:23:03,500
I divined it, even before
the Crystal told me--

312
00:23:03,583 --> 00:23:06,708
He's the samurai who's
going to save our village!

313
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:18,083
♪ closing song ♪

314
00:25:23,125 --> 00:25:26,125
[KOMACHI] Dear Okara.
Hey, it's me, Komachi!

315
00:25:26,208 --> 00:25:27,541
Everything okay?

316
00:25:27,625 --> 00:25:31,458
I promised I'd write once
we got in, so here it is!

317
00:25:31,541 --> 00:25:33,750
The trip out of the
village was pretty.

318
00:25:33,833 --> 00:25:35,500
The city's name is Kogakyo,

319
00:25:35,583 --> 00:25:37,666
and it's way different
from the country.

320
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:42,375
It's big and noisy and full of
people, and kind of smelly, too.

321
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:45,541
This one guy was even
selling cooked frogs!

322
00:25:45,625 --> 00:25:48,416
I asked sister why the Bandits
have to steal our rice,

323
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:50,666
if there's so much food here.

324
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:54,083
But maybe it's like you said--
the Bandits are so big,

325
00:25:54,166 --> 00:25:58,083
they just have to eat and
eat until all the rice is gone!

326
00:25:58,166 --> 00:26:01,500
Sister says during the
Great War, we fed samurai,

327
00:26:01,583 --> 00:26:04,583
so we've always been
giving food to someone.

328
00:26:04,666 --> 00:26:08,791
But if we grow it all,
how come we have to go hungry?

329
00:26:08,875 --> 00:26:11,375
Well, I guess that's
why we're hiring samurai.

330
00:26:11,458 --> 00:26:13,000
To drive the Bandits out!

331
00:26:13,083 --> 00:26:15,458
I hope I can tell you
more about it soon...!

332
00:26:15,541 --> 00:26:17,083
Bye-bye!

